<HEADLINE> Iranian President Underlines Expansion of Tehran- Sanaa Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
on Sunday called for further expansion and development of bilateral
relations between Iran and Yemen to serve the stability, progress
and security of the region.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting Yemeni Information Minister Abdul
Rahman Muhammad al-Akwa, Khatami said that Iran and Yemen have
deeply-rooted historical ties and common interests.
</P>
<P>
He said, expressing hope that the exchange of visits between the
high ranking officials of the two countries would lead to further
expansion of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Describing Yemen's domestic and foreign policy as "prudent,"
Khatami praised Yemen for attaining unity both within and outside
the country, and supporting the Lebanese people and their movement
against the Israeli occupation.
</P>
<P>
He termed the mutual agreements on information between the two
sides as "positive" and said that there is a very firm
determination in Iran to further consolidate and expand the
relations with Yemen.
</P>
<P>
The Yemeni minister Lauded Khatami's viewpoints on issues of
dialog among civilizations.
</P>
<P>
Every vigilant and informed Muslim should follow the same plan
and way of thinking, he said, also underlining expansion of
cooperation in information between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The minister also brought a written message from Yemeni
President Ali Abdullah Saleh to Khatami.
</P>
<P>
Khatami said that the upcoming visit by Saleh to Iran would be a
turning point in the relations between the two countries. But it is
not clear when Saleh will visit Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
