<HEADLINE> ADB President Visits Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- President of the Asian Development
Bank (ADB) Tadao Chino arrived here Sunday on a three-day visit to
sign the Poverty Reduction Partnership Agreement with Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
This will be the formal beginning of ADB's new Poverty
Reduction Strategy with overriding focus on eradication of extreme
poverty from the Asian and Pacific region in partnership with
governments of its developing member countries.
</P>
<P>
All ADB loans and technical assistance will be expected to
contribute to the reduction of poverty and the projects and
programs will also be designed to accelerate pro-poor growth of
focus on poverty directly.
</P>
<P>
According to the proposed strategy, ADB will increase its
support for human capital development since such investments are
usually the most effective way of breaking the cycle of inter-
generational poverty.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Dhaka, the president will call on Prime
Minister Sheikh Hasina and related ministers to exchange views on
the operational and policy matters of ADB in Bangladesh. He will
also hold talks with the private sector leaders at the Federation
of Bangladesh Chambers of Commerce and Industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
