<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Judge Named to Undertake Reformist Assassination Inquiry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Judiciary has appointed a
conservative judge Hussein Razqandi to probe into the assassination
attempt on the life of Saeed Hajjarian, a close reformist ally of
moderate President Mohammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made by Judiciary Chief Ayatollah Mohmoud
Hashemi and head of the Tehran Justice Department, the Islamic
Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
An informed source at the judiciary told IRNA that Razqandi,
former head of the justice department of Varamin, a town south of
Tehran, would chair the Branch 33 of the Tehran Islamic Revolution
Court to deal with the case.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the condition of anonymity, the source said that
Razqandi, holding a special notice, can look into all charges
against those being accused of involvement in the assassination
attempt.
</P>
<P>
The judicial inquiry into the case of agents involved in the
assassination incident are in their final stages, he added.
</P>
<P>
Hajjarian, deputy chairman of Tehran Municipal Council, was shot
and severely wounded in front of the council building on March 12
as tensions ran high following the landslide victory of reformers
over their conservative opponents in February's sensitive
parliament elections.
</P>
<P>
Hajjarian, also managing director of the reformist daily Sobh-e
Emrouz (This Morning) and a former Intelligence Minister, played an
important role in reformers' victory in the elections, which
humiliated the powerful conservatives.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Intelligence Minister Ali Yunesi said last month that 10
people had been arrested in connection with the assassination
attempt. But he said that the assassins are not affiliated with any
group or guild or foreigners, and they had carried out the
assassination attempt on their own and out of personal feelings and
motivations.
</P>
<P>
However, widespread rumors believed that the assassination
attempt was a revenge against Hajjarian by the conservatives who
still dominate the country's most sensitive organs.
</P>
<P>
Some prominent reformist leaders said that the assassination
attempt was linked with certain institutions and vowed to find out
the "commanding headquarters of political assassinations." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
