<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Prime Minister to Visit United States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina will visit the United States from April 4 to 10, Foreign
Secretary C.M. Shafi Sami announced here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Briefing newsmen here, he said that at the invitation of the
President of the Harvard University Neil L. Rudenstin, Sheikh
Hasina will address a selected gathering in the Forum at the John
F.Kennedy School of Government on April 5 on the subject "Leading
a Country in Transition: Challenges and Opportunities."
</P>
<P>
Besides, the Randolph-Macon Woman's College at Lynchburg,
Virginia, has also selected Sheikh Hasina as the winner of the
Randolph-Macon Woman's College Pearl S. Buck Award for 1999.
</P>
<P>
The selection of Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina for the award is
"an acknowledgment of her vision and courage and for her
achievements in the political, economic and humanitarian spheres
which captures the spirit of the award and of the woman who
inspired it," Shafi Sami said.
</P>
<P>
Against the backdrop of the visit of U.S. President Clinton to
Bangladesh on March 20, the current visit of the prime minister
would be yet another opportunity to build on the favorable
impression that Americans have about Bangladesh today, Shafi Sami
said, adding that this would further strengthen the bilateral
relations between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
