<HEADLINE> Quake Hits Southwestern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.1 on the
open-ended Richter scale jolted a wide area of southwestern Japan
centering on Ehime and Miyazaki prefectures Sunday night, the
Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damage, and no tsunami or
tidal wave warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at 9:25 p.m. (local time), was also
felt in neighboring prefectures such as Hiroshima, Okayama,
Kagawa, Kochi and Oita, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was estimated at 150 kilometers
underground in the northern part of Miyazaki Prefecture, the
agency said. 
</P>
