<HEADLINE> New Bureau to Monitor Coal Mine Safety in Liaoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A special bureau has been set up
in northeast China's Liaoning Province to improve safety in local
coal mines.
</P>
<P>
As the first of its kind, the bureau will focus on enacting and
implementing regulations concerning safe mining operations, said
Yuan Zhenduo, head of the bureau, but will not interfere in the
daily management of mines.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning is one of the country's major coal-production bases.
</P>
<P>
The bureau is to carry out thorough checks of installations,
machinery and materials in all the coal mines in the province. It
will also hold a series of training courses so as to raise the
safety awareness of mining personnel.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that similar bureaus will be established in the
other 18 coal-rich provinces in northeast, northwest and southwest
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
