<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Improves Breast Cancer Detection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- China has greatly enhanced the
accuracy of detecting early-stage breast cancer.
</P>
<P>
A new method developed recently by the Shanghai Dongfang Breast
Disease Hospital uses digital positioning technology to detect
tumors with diameters less than 0.5 millimeters. The method also
makes it possible to remove tiny tumors with the probing needle.
</P>
<P>
In the early stage, some breast tumors are too small to be felt
by hand, and x-ray films cannot show the precise position of such
tumors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
