<HEADLINE> Girl Gets Compensation for Tiger Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A five-year-old girl attacked by
a tiger in a local wildlife park received 18,000 yuan (about 2,176
US dollars) in compensation here over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Wildlife Park accepted the ruling by a local court,
and agreed to pay Shen Zhengyu 8,000 yuan in medical,
transportation costs and 10,000 yuan as compensation for
psychological damage.
</P>
<P>
Shen was attacked by a tiger, which scratched her face when
visiting the wildlife park on November 16, 1999.
</P>
<P>
A bus driver was killed by another tiger in the park on the
following day. This incident is being dealt with in a separate
court case.
</P>
<P>
The park has beefed up its security precautions in the wake of
the two incidents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
