<HEADLINE> 4-Year-Old Child Undergoes Esophagoscopy Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Doctors at the Riyadh-based Hamady
hospital performed a rare esophagoscopy operation on a four-year-
old child, the first of its kind in the Gulf and the Middle East,
the Al-ektissadiya daily reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, which did not say when the operation
was performed, the child was suffering from malfunction of the hole
from which esophagus enters abdomen, causing the return of a part
of the stomach to the chest.
</P>
<P>
The 90-minute operation, performed within the context of the
hospital's training medical course of esophagoscopy surgery for
children, was followed by another small operation at the bottom of
the child's stomach. Both operations proved to be successful.
</P>
<P>
Doctors repaired the affected part by making small holes in the
abdomen whose lengths ranged from 0.5 to 1 millimeter.
</P>
<P>
The patient left the hospital the next day, said the report.
</P>
</TEXT>
