<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Opposes Eritrea's Proposal to Establish Flight Information Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia has opposed Eritrea's
recent proposal to establish its flight information region (FIR)
and to amend Africa Indian Ocean Air Navigation Plan, the
Ministry of Transport and Communications said.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency Sunday quoted a statement by the
ministry as saying that Ethiopia rejected Asmara's proposal
because it was a threat to the air space management and flight
security of the Red Sea area flight zone.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia also objected Eritrea's proposal to amend the
Africa-Indian Ocean Air Navigation Plan taking into consideration
technical, operational, legal and aviation security reasons, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia believes that Eritrea's FIR could be established only
in accordance with the International Civil Aviation Convention
that restricts Asmara's FIR to its air space, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting held in Montreal, Canada, on March 8, 2000, the
Council of International Civil Aviation Organization (ICAO)
decided that Eritrea's FIR would come into effect after a
technical discussion that considers the current Ethio-Eritrean
border dispute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
