<HEADLINE> Public Security Head Urges More Fire Awareness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Jia Chunwang, minister of public
security, has urged localities to act swiftly and take every
possible measure to prevent outbreaks of fire disasters that may
cause mass injury and death.
</P>
<P>
He made the call at a nationwide tele-conference on fire
prevention held here today, following a severe fire that broke out
on March 29 and killed 74 people in Jiaozuo City in central China'
s Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that so far this year the country has suffered
13 major fire disasters, resulting in the loss of 142 lives,
leaving 105 people injured and causing 30 million yuan in economic
losses.
</P>
<P>
Jia ordered local public security departments to make fire
prevention their top priority, and carry out detailed
investigations into the causes of fires.
</P>
<P>
People held responsible for fires must be strictly punished, Jia
said, adding that the departments concerned should also improve
the general public's awareness of the importance of fire
prevention, and strengthen control and supervision of personnel in
charge of fighting fires and preventing their occurrence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
