<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Reduces Enterprise Burden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
has punished 1,400 officials over the last three years for levying
illegal charges on enterprises, according to provincial officials.
</P>
<P>
In the handling of 4,800 cases involving such levies on
enterprises, the province has saved 190 million yuan for the
enterprises concerned, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Following the instructions of the State Council, the province
has established special organizations to deal with illegal charges.
</P>
<P>
In Luohe City, 44 retired officials were sent to 41 major
enterprises to protect them against illegal charges.
</P>
<P>
Over the three years, the province canceled a total of 5,901
levies, saving nearly 1.7 billion yuan a year. 
