for Tourism,
</P>
<P>
Trade and Industry has said that his country supported the ban
on ivory trade.
</P>
<P>
The minister made the remarks in a written speech Saturday read
by Kenya Tourism Board Chairman Uhuru Kenyatta during the
Convention on the International Trade in Endangered Species
(Cites) open day held at the Nairobi National Museum.
</P>
