<HEADLINE> Africa-Europe Foreign Ministers Meeting 06pens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers from African and
European countries met Sunday ahead of the Africa-Europe summit to
finalize the agenda that will be discussed at the summit.
</P>
<P>
The summit, sponsored by the Organization of African Unity and
the European Union, is to discuss economic, political and social
development issues and bilateral cooperation in these fields.
</P>
<P>
But before the meeting, African and EU countries differed over
which issues should take priority in the upcoming discussion.
</P>
<P>
African countries want the summit to focus on the concerns of
Africa, such as debts, poverty and dieases. But EU leaders hope
provention of conflicts, democracy and human rights will be mainly
addressed at the summit.
</P>
<P>
The two-day summit on April 3-4, the first of its kind, involves
heads of state and government, and representatives from 53 African
countries and 15 EU member states. 
</P>
