<HEADLINE> McRae Retains Lead despite Penalty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Colin McRae of Scotland kept a
narrow lead over Richard Burns in the Catalunya Rally with three
special stages left on Sunday despite a ten second penalty.
</P>
<P>
McRae, who drove the Ford Focus with a 4.3 second lead over his
Subaru rival overnight, took the final day's opening special but
was penalised after his car suffered clutch problems, narrowing
his advantage to just 1.3 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Burns, who won in Portugal and Kenya, finished second in the
12th stage, 7 seconds behind the 1995 world champion.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Sainz, in the other Ford Focus, lies 7.7 seconds behind
his teammate. 
