<P>
An angry CAFA and FIFA executive member, Ismael Bhamjee, said
that no decisin has been made on who CAFA will endorse in Africa
and CAFA President Issa Hayatou was annoyed with the reports in
the South African media that he has told the Moroccan king Morocco
"had no chance" of hosting the great sporting event.
</P>
<P>
"I spoke with Hayatou soon after he had read the story, and he
was very upset. He wanted to know how he wound possibly have gone
into the king's palace and told him his country had no chance in
the 2006 race-- it would be an insult," Bhamjee said.
</P>
<P>
The false reports cound actually jeopardize South Africa's bid
rather than aid it and local journalists should follow basic
principles and check their facts before they write stories,
Bhamjee stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
