<DOCNO> XIE20000402.0098 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suspects Responsible for Cinema Fire Detained </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Police in Jiaozuo City in
central China's Henan Province have detained more than 12 suspects
who are held responsible for a fire that broke out on March 29 and
killed 74 people.
</P>
<P>
Detained by the police were the boss of the video parlor Han
Benyu, 11 employees of the video parlor and Zhao Suxia, a public
security official in charge of the fire safety matters in the
district where the video parlor is located.
</P>
<P>
The police said the fire was caused by an overheated quartz
heater in the Tiantang video parlor, or Heaven video parlor in
English.
</P>
<P>
Investigations show that the video parlor lacks necessary fire
control facilities and has been opened without approval from the
local fire control authorities.
</P>
<P>
The predecessor of the video parlor is a food store under the
city's vegetables and foodstuff company, which was in 1998
contracted to Han Benyu and transformed into a video parlor with
two video halls and 28 VIP entertainment rooms.
</P>
<P>
The police said the bodies of the fire victims are so severely
burnt that only 16 of them have been identified by their relatives
so far. Related departments are still working to help the
relatives of other victims identify the rest of the bodies.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
