<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nanjing Puts Limit on Construction of High Buildings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The historical city of Nanjing,
capital of Jiangsu Province, will put limit on the height of
buildings in the future.
</P>
<P>
With a history of 2,500 years, the city of Nanjing in east
China ranks fifth among the big cities that have the largest
number of skyscrapers in China following Beijing, Shanghai,
Guangzhou and Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
However, the city had only two seven-story buildings before the
People's Republic of China was founded in 1949.
</P>
<P>
Wang Hongmin, the city mayor, said that the city should not
build any more high buildings without careful planning because it
is likely to lose the beauty of a garden city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
