<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills 11 People in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were killed and 44
injured Saturday when the bus they were travelling veered off the
road and plunged into a river in Kisii, a town in western Kenya,
local media reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Five people escaped the road accident which occurred at Keumbu
area along the Kisii-Nairobi highway, and the 44 injured were
admitted to the Kisii district general hospital.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened barely three days after two buses
collided last Wednesday along the Kericho-Nakuru road in the
western part of the country, killing 76 people in Kenya's worst
road accident.
</P>
<P>
Police at the scene said five men and two women died on the
spot while four other men including the driver died on the
arrival to the hospital.
</P>
<P>
According to an eyewitness, the bus was travelling at a high
speed when it lost control while negotiating a corner and landed
into river where it rammed onto several trees.
</P>
<P>
Following the Wednesday bus crash, Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi Thursday ordered police to set up road blocks to stop
overloaded and over- sped buses to minimize road carnage and to
help save more lives in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
