<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, April 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA -- About 1,200 Indians of the Uwa community of Colombia
occupied Cubara in the Andea region of Boyaca to demand the
government cancel the license granted to Occidental Petroleum (Oxy)
to explore the area adjacent to the Indian settlement, the ethnic
group said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Uwa spokesman Fabio Tegria said that it is "a peaceful
occupation of undefined duration" to protest the government's
granting to the multinational Oxy an environmental permit to
explore the Samore block next to the Uwa reservation in Boyaca.(
Colombia-Indians)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BOGOTA -- Two soldiers and a rebel woman were killed Saturday
in fighting in Colombia's northeast Santander department, military
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
A corporal was injured and four rebels captured Saturday when
the army chased the People's Liberation Army (EPL) rebels in
Rionegro rural area, some 400 kilometers northeast of Bogota, said
General Martin Carreno, chief of the Fifth Army Brigade deployed
in Bucaramanga.
</P>
<P>
During the fighting with the EPL, a lesser rebel group which
was demobilized in 1991, the army seized two rifles, eight
motorcycles, two automobiles and food rations, he said. (Colombia-
Rebel-Fighting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistan and Iran will hold a deputy minister-
level meeting with a view to chalking out a plan for a joint
effort to bring peace to their war-worn neighbor Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Foreign Minister of Iran Mohsin Aminzada is arriving
here next week to hold formal talks on Afghanistan with his
Pakistani counterpart, Inam-ul-Haq, official sources said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and Iran have often found themselves supporting
opposing forces in the Afghan conflict and they differ in their
perceptions on the Afghan issue.
</P>
<P>
During the course of Afghan conflict Islamabad has supported
the ruing Taliban militia, while Tehran backs the anti-Taliban
Northern Alliance. (Pakistan-Iran-Afghanistan) 
</P>
</TEXT>
