<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Sell Textiles Online </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading textile
producer, has decided to sell its textiles online.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has just established a special e-commerce company,
Longtou Zhangjiang Commercial Network Company Limited, with an
initial investment of 10 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Raw materials such as cotton and chemical fiber will be also
available via the Net.
</P>
<P>
Going online is part of Shanghai's effort to make the textile
industry highly profitable again after its major restructuring
over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
China's textile industry was over-staffed and inefficient. A
three-year reform program began in 1998 to help the industry
become profitable.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, outdated machinery and equipment including
10 million of China's 46 million spindles in cotton mills are
expected to be scrapped to cut down production capacity and
increase efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has closed 185 cotton mills and reduced its number of
spindles from 2.5 million to less than one million.
</P>
<P>
Last year Shanghai reported 15.8 billion yuan in textile sales,
with profits amounting to about 200 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
