<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Iran will hold a
deputy minister-level meeting with a view to chalking out a plan
for a joint effort to bring peace to their war-worn neighbor
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Foreign Minister of Iran Mohsin Aminzada is arriving
here next week to hold formal talks on Afghanistan with his
Pakistani counterpart, Inam-ul-Haq, official sources said Sunday.
</P>
