<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Rate Rises to 43-Week High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- India's inflation rate rose to a
43-week high of 3.74 percent for the week ending on March 16, due
to a sharp rise in the prices of natural gas and oil.
</P>
<P>
According to the Reserve Bank of India, the 0.24 percentage
point rise in the annual inflation rate to 3.74 percent compared
with 3.5 percent in the previous week was triggered mainly by a 1.
2-percent jump in the price index for fuel, power, light and
lubricants.
</P>
<P>
The Inflation rate during the corresponding week last year was
4.87 percent.
</P>
<P>
Officials indicated that the upward momentum in the inflation
rate is likely to persist in the coming weeks with various
budgetary measures put into force on April 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
