<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Booms in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Latest statistics show that the
total foreign investment in Beijing increased by 1.6 percent on a
year-on-year basis in the first two months of this year to hit 295
million US dollars in contractual value.
</P>
<P>
According to sources with the Beijing Municipal Committee of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, the national capital newly
approved 127 overseas-funded ventures in the first two months and
most of the overseas investors came from the United States, Japan
and the European Union.
</P>
<P>
It is said that this year, the Beijing Municipal government
will encourage more foreign cash flow in high technology projects
in Zhongguancun area of Beijing and the construction of urban
infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
The city will also adopt more favorable policies in taxation to
encourage overseas-funded enterprises to purchase more
domestically-made products and further expand investment in China.
</P>
<P>
In the first two months, 43 foreign-funded ventures in Beijing
further increased their investment by 111 million dollars.
</P>
