biggest exporter of textile products and garments: it registered a
record-high export turnover of 45.6 billion US dollars in 1997;
although its export of such products declined to 43.1 billion US
dollars in 1998 as a result of the Asian financial crisis, the
amount still accounted for more than 13 percent of the world's
total.
</P>
