<TEXT>
<P>
China has scored obvious achievements in basic education for
all of its people in the past decade, including giving education a
position of priority on the government's working agenda, an
official with the Ministry of Education said on March 30 in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Lin Zhihua, an official from the ministry's Development and
Planning Department, made this remark at the seminar "Basic
Education Forum -- Education for All: Progress since 1990 and
Challenges Ahead."
</P>
<P>
Lin said that China has scored great achievements in developing
pre-school education, enlarging the basic education enrollment
rate, and reducing the youth illiteracy rate from 10.4 percent in
1990 to five percent last year.
</P>
<P>
 Top Fine Arts Academy to Relocate
</P>
<P>
The Central Academy of Fine Arts, the cradle of Chinese
painters, will soon end its embarrassing situation of being in a
factory-owned building, and will relocate to a 13.3-hectare venue
in northeast Beijing this September.
</P>
<P>
The new school will be located at the Wangjing New Quarter and
will cover an area six times that of its original place. The
academy will include a teaching building, library, and multi-
functional and designing buildings.
</P>
<P>
First Postgraduates of Beijing Opera Hold Graduation Ceremony
</P>
<P>
The first class of postgraduate students studying the Peking
Opera held their graduation ceremony on March 29.
</P>
<P>
In October 1996, the 26-member postgraduate class was approved
by the Ministry of Culture and sponsored by the Academy of Chinese
Operas.
</P>
<P>
45,000 University Graduates to Go to Countryside in 3 Years
</P>
<P>
China will send 15,000 university graduates to work in rural
areas this year as part of the plan to send 45,000 of them to help
rural development at the grassroots level in three years beginning
1999.
</P>
<P>
It is also an effort to broaden the areas for the employment of
university graduates and allow the countryside to have more
talented people, according to an official of the Ministry of
Personnel.
</P>
<P>
A large number of university students have applied for the
assignment, and so far, 15,284 graduates have been chosen, he
added.  
