<HEADLINE> Asian Boxing Olympic Qualifying Tournament Begins at Bangkok </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The 3rd Asian qualifying boxing
tournament for the Sydney Olympic Games started Saturday here in
the Mall Convention Hall, with over 200 participators from 31
Asian countries and regions compete for the entry to the Olympiad.
</P>
<P>
The tournament covers 12 categories form Light Fly Weight (48
kg) to Super Heavy Weight (91+kg), and each team can only enter
one boxer for each category. The boxers who are qualified from the
First and Second tournament in Tashkent and Seoul are not allowed
to participate in this tournament.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the boxing associations of each team can enter the
boxer(s) only into the weight class that their boxer(s) in which
is (are) not yet qualified. The tournament will proceed from 1
April to 7 April, and will provide Gold, Silver and two Bronze
awards. The quota of qualifiers for Asian boxers to enter the 2000
Olympic Games is 66, and the 42 qualifiers have been created
during the former two tournaments. 
