<HEADLINE> Syria, UAE Sign 2 Accords on Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Syria and the United Arab Emirates
(UAE) on Sunday agree to set up a free trade zone between the two
countries and further economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two accords in this regard were signed here by Syrian
Minister of Economy and Foreign Trade Mohammed Al Imadi and
visiting UAE Minister of Economy and Commerce Sheikh Fahim Al
Qasimi.
</P>
<P>
The first document provides for the liberalization of trade and
creating a free zone between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The second encourages the export-import of agricultural,
industrial and animal products and the movement of capital between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The document also stresses the need to abide by the Single Arab
Capital Investment Agreement which protects bilateral investments
from confiscation.
</P>
<P>
Qasimi arrived here on Saturday on a two-day visit to Syria.
